Open Source Success Stories¶



  • PostgreSQL: powerful, extensible, analytical RDBMS

    • Community: contributors, mailing lists, local user groups

  • Python: general purpose, extensible language

    • PyPI: repository of modules

  • R: data science stack, extensible environment

    • CRAN: repository of packages

Challenging Commercial Market Share




Relational Database Solution

  • Data persistence: historical and current needs

  • Maintenance/hygiene: adherence to types

  • Storage efficiency: normalization reduces repetition of data

  • Centralization: multiple user environment and security

  • Scalability: not limited to local resources

Use Case: Environment Data

Human Impact on the Global and Local Biosphere and Climate

CREATE TABLE global_temperature (
   id SERIAL NOT NULL PRIMARY KEY,
   year INT,
   period VARCHAR(50),
   global_mean NUMERIC(5,2)
);

COPY global_temperature (year, period, global_mean) FROM '/home/parfaitg/Databases/ENVIRONMENT/global_temperature.csv' WITH CSV HEADER DELIMITER AS ',';

COMMENT ON TABLE global_temperature IS 'Source: NASA - Combined Land-Surface Air and Sea-Surface Water Temperature Anomalies (Land-Ocean Temperature Index, LOTI) (https://data.giss.nasa.gov/gistemp/)';

%%sql resultset <<
WITH temp_sub AS (
             SELECT year AS date_year, 
                    CASE period
                         WHEN 'Jan' THEN 1
                         WHEN 'Feb' THEN 2
                         WHEN 'Mar' THEN 3
                         WHEN 'Apr' THEN 4
                         WHEN 'May' THEN 5
                         WHEN 'Jun' THEN 6
                         WHEN 'Jul' THEN 7
                         WHEN 'Aug' THEN 8
                         WHEN 'Sep' THEN 9
                         WHEN 'Oct' THEN 10
                         WHEN 'Nov' THEN 11
                         WHEN 'Dec' THEN 12
                   END::int AS date_month,
                   global_mean 
            FROM global_temperature
         ),
             agg_sea_ice AS (
              SELECT date_year, date_month, region,
                     AVG(extent) AS avg_extent
              FROM sea_ice_extent
              GROUP BY date_year, date_month, region
         )
      
         
         SELECT CONCAT(s.date_year, '-', s.date_month, '-01')::timestamp as "date", 
                s.avg_extent::float AS "Avg Artic Sea Ice Extent",
                n.avg_extent::float AS "Avg Anatartica Sea Ice Extent",
                t.global_mean::float AS "Global Mean Temp Anomaly"
         FROM agg_sea_ice s
         JOIN agg_sea_ice n
           ON s.date_year = n.date_year AND s.date_month = n.date_month 
          AND s.region = 'Antarctica' AND n.region = 'Arctic'         
         JOIN temp_sub t
           ON s.date_year = t.date_year AND s.date_month = t.date_month

sql = """SELECT CONCAT(o.year::int, '-', o.month::int, '-', 1)::date as "date",
                AVG(o.phts25p0) AS "pH at total scale, 25C and 0 dbar",
                AVG(o.phtsinsitutp) AS "pH at total scale, in situ"
         FROM ocean_data o
         WHERE o.phts25p0 <> -9999 AND o.phtsinsitutp <> -9999
         GROUP BY CONCAT(o.year::int, '-', o.month::int, '-', 1)::date
         ORDER BY CONCAT(o.year::int, '-', o.month::int, '-', 1)::date
      """

ocean_df = pd.read_sql(sql, conn, index_col=['date'], parse_dates=['date'])

def run_decomp(col):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(4, 1, figsize=(15,7), sharex=True)

    series = ocean_df[col].resample('m').sum()

    sd = seasonal_decompose(series, model='additive')

    sd.observed.plot(ax=ax[0], legend=False, color=seaborn_palette[0])
    ax[0].set_title("{} - Level".format(col), fontsize=18, fontweight='bold')
    ax[0].set_ylabel('Observed')
    sd.trend.plot(ax=ax[1], legend=False, color=seaborn_palette[1])
    ax[1].set_ylabel('Trend')
    sd.seasonal.plot(ax=ax[2], legend=False, color=seaborn_palette[2])
    ax[2].set_ylabel('Seasonal')
    sd.resid.plot(ax=ax[3], legend=False, color=seaborn_palette[3])
    ax[3].set_ylabel('Residual')

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()
    plt.clf()
    plt.close()
    
run_decomp('pH at total scale, 25C and 0 dbar')

sql = """WITH land AS (
             SELECT year, 
                    percent_arable
             FROM arable_land
             WHERE country_name = 'World'
        ), pop AS (
             SELECT year, 
                    (population / 1E6) as population
             FROM world_population
             WHERE country_name = 'World'
        )

        SELECT l.year, l.percent_arable, p.population
        FROM land l
        INNER JOIN pop p ON l.year = p.year              
      """

arable_df = pd.read_sql(sql, conn, index_col='year')

def graph_fct(df, main, series1, col1, title1, series2, col2, title2):
    with plt.rc_context({'ytick.color':  col1}):
       fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12,5))
       df.reindex([series1], axis=1).plot(kind='line', ax=ax, color = col1)
       ax.set_ylabel(title1, color =  col1)
       
    with plt.rc_context({'ytick.color': col2}):
       df.reindex([series2], axis=1).plot(kind='line', ax=ax, secondary_y=True, color = col2)   
       ax.right_ax.set_ylabel(title2, color = col2)
    
    lns = ax.get_lines() + ax.right_ax.get_lines()
    labs = [l.get_label() for l in lns]
    ax.legend(lns, labs, loc=0)
    
    plt.title(main, fontsize=18, fontweight='bold')
    plt.tight_layout()
    
    plt.show()
    plt.clf()
    plt.close()    
    
    
graph_fct(df=arable_df, main="Arable Land vs World Population",
          series1="percent_arable", col1=seaborn_palette[3], title1="Average Arable Land (%)",
          series2="population", col2=seaborn_palette[0], title2="World Population (millions)")

sql = """SELECT a.year,
                SUM(a.percent_arable) FILTER(WHERE a.country_name = 'Argentina')     AS "Argentina",
                SUM(a.percent_arable) FILTER(WHERE a.country_name = 'Nigeria')       AS "Nigeria",

                SUM(a.percent_arable) FILTER(WHERE a.country_name = 'Germany')       AS "Germany",

                SUM(a.percent_arable) FILTER(WHERE a.country_name = 'China')         AS "China",
                SUM(a.percent_arable) FILTER(WHERE a.country_name = 'Saudi Arabia')  AS "Saudi Arabia"
         FROM arable_land a

World Annual Environment Metrics

In [81]:
sql = """WITH pop AS 
            (SELECT p.year,
                    p.population
             FROM world_population p
             WHERE p.country_name = 'World'
               AND p.year BETWEEN 2000 AND 2019
             ),
              
              land AS
            (SELECT a.year,
                    a.percent_arable
             FROM arable_land a
             WHERE a.country_name = 'World'
               AND a.year BETWEEN 2000 AND 2019
             ),
         
              fauna AS
            (SELECT i.year,
                    SUM(i.species_count) AS animals_count
             FROM iucn_species_count i
             WHERE i.year BETWEEN 2000 AND 2019
             GROUP BY i.year
             ),
         
              flora AS
            (SELECT p.assessment_year as year,
                    COUNT(*) AS plants_count
             FROM plants_assessments p
             WHERE p.assessment_year BETWEEN 2000 AND 2019
               AND p.interpreted_status = 'Threatened'
             GROUP BY p.assessment_year
             ),             
         
              ice AS
            (SELECT s.date_year as year,
                    AVG(s.extent) FILTER(WHERE s.region = 'Arctic') AS arctic_sea_ice_extent,
                    AVG(s.extent) FILTER(WHERE s.region = 'Antarctica') AS antarctic_sea_ice_extent
             FROM sea_ice_extent s
             WHERE s.date_year BETWEEN 2000 AND 2019
             GROUP BY s.date_year
             ),
             
              ocean AS
            (SELECT o.year as year,
                    AVG(o.tco2) AS total_co2,
                    AVG(o.phts25p0) AS phts25p0
             FROM ocean_data o
             WHERE o.year BETWEEN 2000 AND 2019
               AND o.tco2 <> -9999 AND o.phts25p0 <> -9999
             GROUP BY o.year
             ),
             
              temp AS
            (SELECT g.year as year,
                    AVG(g.global_mean) AS global_mean
             FROM global_temperature g
             WHERE g.year BETWEEN 2000 AND 2019
             GROUP BY g.year
             )
             
         SELECT pop.year, pop.population, land.percent_arable, fauna.animals_count, flora.plants_count,
                ice.arctic_sea_ice_extent, ice.antarctic_sea_ice_extent, 
                ocean.total_co2, ocean.phts25p0, temp.global_mean
         FROM pop 
         JOIN land USING (year)
         JOIN fauna USING (year)
         JOIN flora USING (year)
         JOIN ice USING (year)
         JOIN ocean USING (year)
         JOIN temp USING (year)
         ORDER BY pop.year
      """

env_year_df = pd.read_sql(sql, conn)
env_year_df
